1. üöó Scenario: Vehicle Rental Management System with User Management
The ABC Rental Company wants you (the programmer) to build a Vehicle Rental System that supports:

üë§ User Management
Users must be able to register

Users must be able to log in

User data must be saved to a file

Each user has:

username

password

list of rentals they have made (Composition)

üöò Main Business Requirement: Vehicle Rentals
The system must also:

Allow logged-in users to Rent Vehicles

Allow users to View Their Rentals

Admin role (special user) can:

Add Vehicles

Delete Vehicles

View all vehicles

Vehicles should be loaded from a file on start, and saved on exit.

üì¶ Key Relationships (Composition)
RentalSystem HAS Users

RentalSystem HAS Vehicles

User HAS Rentals

Rental HAS a Vehicle + rental date

Vehicle HAS details (type, model, price)

üß± What Students Must Build (Instructions)
1Ô∏è‚É£ Create a User class
    Fields:

    username

    password

    ArrayList<Rental> rentals

    Methods:

    addRental(Rental r)

    showRentals()

2Ô∏è‚É£ Create a Vehicle class
    Fields:

    id

    model

    type (Car, Motorbike, Truck)

    pricePerDay

    Method to display vehicle info.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Create a Rental class
    Fields:

    rentedVehicle (Vehicle object)

    rentalDate (String)

    Composition:
    A Rental HAS a Vehicle.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Create a RentalSystem class
    This class should manage:

    ArrayList<User> users

    ArrayList<Vehicle> vehicles

    Methods:

    registerUser()

    loginUser()

    addVehicle()

    deleteVehicle()

    showVehicles()

    rentVehicle()

    saveUsersToFile()

    loadUsersFromFile()

    saveVehiclesToFile()

    loadVehiclesFromFile()

  Create Main class (menu system)
1. Register
2. Login
3. Exit

  If logged in as normal user:
1. Rent Vehicle
2. View My Rentals
3. Logout

  If logged in as admin:
1. Add Vehicle
2. Delete Vehicle
3. List Vehicles
4. Logout


