1.3 QUESTION FOR STUDENTS (Assignment)
    Scenario-Based Task: Manage Vehicle Availability
    You are upgrading the Vehicle Rental System.
    The rental company has asked you to add Vehicle Availability Management.

    New Requirements
    Every vehicle must have an availability flag:

    true ‚Üí Available

    false ‚Üí Rented

    When a user rents a vehicle:

    Mark that vehicle as not available

    When listing vehicles:
    Show:

    101 - Toyota Corolla (Car) - $45/day - AVAILABLE
    102 - Honda CBR (Motorbike) - $30/day - NOT AVAILABLE
    When renting:

    Only allow renting vehicles that are available

    If the vehicle is not available, show:

    Sorry, this vehicle is already rented.
    Update file saving logic to include availability.

    Update file loading logic to read availability back.

    üí° HINTS FOR STUDENTS
    Add a boolean field:

    boolean available;
    Set default availability to true when adding a vehicle

    In rentVehicle():

    Check if(v.available == false) ‚Üí reject rental

    Otherwise ‚Üí v.available = false;

    When writing to file:

    id,model,type,price,available
    When reading from file:

    Use Boolean.parseBoolean(data[4])

